sources.title: Wake Me When the War Is Over (1969 film) Comedy War | Ken Berry, Eva Gabor
sources.description:
When Love is Blindsided, Lies are Lost in Time.
During the final months of WW2, a lonely German Baroness hides an attractive American airman in her mansion for long time without telling him the war has been over for almost five years.

Original title: Wake Me When the War Is Over (1969)
This film is subtitled in many language options.

Director: Gene Nelson
Writers: Frank Peppiatt, John Aylesworth
Stars: Ken Berry, Eva Gabor, Werner Klemperer
Genres: Classics, Comedy, War


00:00 - Full Movie (with subtitles)
00:18 - An Allied pilot, parachuting into Germany, finds refuge with a widow in WWII.
11:08 - A woman helps a fugitive escape capture as they plot a daring wartime getaway.
19:47 - A WWII comedy involving a Baroness, an American, and the bumbling Gestapo.
29:35 - An American, unaware the war has ended, gets tangled in weekly German war reenactments.
38:31 - Mistaken identities and post-war confusion lead to hilarious chaos for a clueless soldier.
46:05 - A comedic mix-up leads to interrogations and underground activities in WWII.
58:12 - A man and woman race to escape danger in a fast-paced WWII comedy.
